The paper deals with geometric query problems, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The use of preprocessing techniques to efficiently report the largest circle that contains a query point but does not contain any member of a given geometric set suggests that it may also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The study of geometric sets such as point sets and boundaries of simple polygons suggests that it may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The focus on finding the largest circle that satisfies certain conditions suggests that it may also belong to the cs.GR (Computer Graphics) sub-category. Finally, the use of geometric objects to solve a query problem suggests that it may belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
